ZCZC EE01
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SATURDAY TO TUESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND
MARITIME AGENCY AT 242300 UTC
ON SATURDAY EVENING AN AREA OF HIGH PRESSURE CENTRE
1031HPA IS EXP TO LIE OVER THE SERN BRITISH ISLES.
MEANWHILE A LOW PRESSURE CENTRE 982HPA LIES W OF ICELAND
WITH A FRONTAL TROUGH EXTENDING DOWN INTO THE FAR N OF
NITON. THIS FRONTAL TROUGH IS EXP TO TRACK NE CLEARING
NITON THROUGH SUNDAY. MEANWHILE THE HIGH PRESSURE CENTRE
1035HPA DRIFTS SLWY E TO LIE IN THE SERN N SEA BY
SUNDAY. A FURTHER LOW CENTRE 996HPA IS EXP TO DEEPEN TO
THE W OF NITON THROUGH MONDAY AND TRACK N CLEARING THE
AREA BY TUESDAY MORNING. THERE REMAINS SOME UNCERTAINTY
IN THE TRACK OF THIS LOW CENTRE. STRG WINDS ARE EXP
ACROSS SHANNON ON SATURDAY EVENING AND SUNDAY WITH LIGHT
WINDS ELSEWHERE. WINDS ARE THEN EXP TO STRENGTHEN AGAIN
ACROSS SHANNON AND SOLE THROUGH MONDAY AND MAY REACH NEAR
GALE FOR A TIME BEFORE CLEARING TO THE N BY TUKSDAY
MORNING. STRG WINDS MAY ALSO DEVELOP ACROSS FITZROY
THROUGH MONDAY
